    <chapter xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_samplechapter">
        <title>Week 5: Getting About</title>
        <!-- sample taken from page 54: At the Airport -->

        <section xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54">
            <title>Zai jichang</title>
            <subtitle>At the Airport</subtitle>
            

            <para>International flights arrive at most major cities, and there is an extensive
                network of internal flights operating from every provincial capital. Although the
                airport environment is largely universal, it is sometimes useful to be able to
                understand key words and phrases in Chinese.</para>
            <!-- exercise 1: illustrates crossreferencing of parts of phrase entry -->
            <section xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_1_warmup">
                <title>1. Warm Up</title>
                
                <para>Say <inline_phrase_entry>
                        <form><xref condition="dig" cref="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_1_warmup_1"
                                xlink:href="#EWPB_Chinese_test_p24" role="phrase_entry_ref"/>
                            <link condition="prt" cref="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_warmup_1"
                                xlink:href="#EWPB_Chinese_test_p24" role="phrase_entry_ref"
                                >(pp.24–5)</link></form>
                        <sense><def><quote>Would you please help
                        me?</quote></def></sense></inline_phrase_entry>
                </para>
            </section>
            <!-- exercise 2 -->
            <section xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_2">
                <title>2. Words to remember</title>
                <para>Familiarize yourself with these words and test yourself using the flap.</para>
                <phrase_entry xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_2_pe1">
                    <form>
                        <orth>办理登机手续</orth>
                        <pron>banli dengji shouxu</pron>
                    </form>
                    <sense>
                        <def>check-in</def>
                    </sense>
                </phrase_entry>
            </section>
            <!-- section "3. Useful phrases omitted as has the same model as 2." -->
            <section xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_4">
                <!-- exercise 4 -->
                <title>4. Put into practice</title>
                <para>Join in this conversation. Read the Chinese on the left and follow the
                    instructions to make your reply. Then test yourself by concealing the answers
                    with the cover flap.</para>
                <phrase_entry xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_4_pe1">
                    <form>
                        <orth>下次请</orth>
                        <pron>xiayiwei</pron>
                    </form>
                    <sense>
                        <def>Next, please.</def>
                    </sense>
                </phrase_entry>
                <phrase_entry xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_4_pe2">
                    <sense>
                        <def>Ask: Is the plane to Shanghai on time?</def>
                    </sense>
                    <form>
                        <orth>去上海德费基准点码</orth>
                        <pron>qu shanghai de feiji zhundian ma</pron>
                    </form>
                </phrase_entry>
            </section>

            <section xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_5">
                <!-- exercise 5-->
                <title>5. Match and repeat</title>
                <para>Match the numbered items to the Chinese words in the panel.</para>
                <mediaobject xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_5_airport_image">
                    <imageobjectco>
                        <areaspec>
                            <area xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_5_airport_image_co1"
                                coords="150 40 155 45"/>
                        </areaspec>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata
                                fileref="EW_ChinesePhraseBook/EWTG_Chinese_Phrasebook_airport.jpg"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <calloutlist>
                            <callout arearefs="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_5_airport_image_co1">
                                <para><inline_phrase_entry xml:id="EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_5_pe1">
                                        <form>
                                            <orth>登机手</orth>
                                            <pron>dengjipai</pron>
                                        </form>
                                        <sense condition="dig">
                                            <!-- boarding pass is already in the image so only use sense for digital / rich  outputs -->
                                            <def>boarding pass</def>
                                            <link
                                                xlink:href="#EWPB_Chinese_test_p54_5_airport_image_co1"
                                                role="phrase_entry_ref"/>
                                            <!-- optionally use link with role="phrase_entry_ref" to indicate thate the sense/definition is in the image -->
                                        </sense>
                                    </inline_phrase_entry></para>

                            </callout>
                        </calloutlist>

                    </imageobjectco>
                </mediaobject>
                <sidebar>
                    <title>Read it</title>
                    <para> Chinese takes basic concepts and combines them to make different
                        meanings, e.g.<inline_phrase_entry>
                            <form>
                                <orth>飞</orth>
                                <pron>feiji</pron>
                            </form>
                            <sense><quote>plane</quote></sense>
                        </inline_phrase_entry>(<inline_phrase_entry>
                            <sense><quote>flying</quote></sense>
                            <form>
                                <orth>飞</orth>
                                <pron>fei</pron>
                            </form>
                        </inline_phrase_entry>+<inline_phrase_entry>
                            <sense><quote>machine</quote></sense>
                            <form>
                                <orth>机</orth>
                                <pron>ji</pron>
                            </form>
                        </inline_phrase_entry>);
                        <!-- 2nd example skipped as it follows the same model -->
                    </para>
                </sidebar>
            </section>



        </section>






